adjectives.description: geostrategic (comparative more geostrategic, superlative most geostrategic)

entries.meaning: Pertaining to the strategy of dealing with geopolitical issues; geopolitically strategic. [from 20th c.]
examples: Once in possession of Istanbul, the Russians would control the geostrategic straits of the Bosporus and the Dardanelles linking Russia's Black Sea ports to the Mediterranean.
